        <font size='4'><b>TIME TO GEAR UP FOR NEW YEAR'S EVE</b></font><br>
                                <img src='http://graphics.millsberry.com/site_gfx/interiors/gazette/gazette_20081223.jpg' border='1' width='280' height='200'>
                        </div>
        <div id='gazette_byline'><em>By Audrey Smythe-Wei<br>Editor-in-Chief</em></div>
        <b>Tuesday, December 23, 2008</b> &mdash;
    The end of the year is almost here, and you know what that means: Party time!<br><br>With 2008 winding down, everyone in Millsberry has been busy getting things in order for their New Year&#039;s Eve celebrations. <br><br><a href="http://www.millsberry.com/shop.phtml?shop_id=7">Many spent time collecting decorations</a>, party favors, and <a href="http://www.millsberry.com/shop.phtml?shop_id=1">other essentials</a>, in preparation for the big night. And excitement about several different New Year&#039;s Eve parties has quickly spread around town.  <br><br>The gathering creating the most buzz is Edna Nelson&#039;s dance party at Town Hall. <br><br>When asked about her party, Edna commented, &quot;Some people think being old is just about sitting in rocking chairs and knitting things, but I enjoy breaking it down just like everyone else.&quot;<br><br>&quot;I&#039;m even having Recording Studio guru, Tony &#039;Tee-Ray&#039; DJ the party,&quot; she added. <br><br>Over at the Recording Studio, Tony &quot;Tee-Ray&quot; was still thumbing through albums in preparation for the gig. <br>
<br>
&quot;Edna has excellent taste in music,&quot; Tony said. &quot;She even helped me pick out a few tracks.&quot; <br><br>&quot;Just because she&#039;s the curator of the Historical Society doesn&#039;t mean her taste in music is historic,&quot; he added.<br><br>Meanwhile, at Wearhouse, Loretta Rivers was picking out the perfect accessories for the night&#039;s festivities.<br><br>&quot;There was one party where Edna challenged me to a dance-off. I held my own for a while, but in the end I couldn&#039;t keep up. She may not look it, but she&#039;s got some moves,&quot; said Loretta. <br><br>Laslo Balint recalled some of his own experiences with Edna and her dancing feet. <br><br>&quot;We were having a charity dance-marathon,&quot; Laslo said. &quot;Edna ended up being the last one standing. She even created her own signature move that night, the &#039;Edna Nelson.&#039;&quot;<br><br>Then Laslo attempted to demonstrate Edna&#039;s move. <br><br>&quot;I can&#039;t really do it justice,&quot; he said. &quot;It was way more impressive at the time.&quot;<br><br>Back at Town Hall, Edna was still preparing for her party. <br><br>&quot;The floor&#039;s going to have to be a little slick if there&#039;s going to be any break-dancing,&quot; Edna yelled over the noise, while operating her floor-waxing machine. &quot;This is going to be a great New Year&#039;s!&quot;<br><br>Time to get ready for the big night. It&#039;s sure to be the party of the year! <br>
    </div>

